    <h1 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">SSGC Bill Check Online — Sui Southern Gas Bill 2026</h1>

    <p class="text-neutral-600 text-lg mb-4"><strong>Sui Southern Gas Company (SSGC)</strong> is Pakistan's second-largest natural gas utility, supplying piped gas to <strong>over 3.4 million consumers</strong> across Sindh and Balochistan (SNGPL handles Punjab, KP, and AJK). With winters driving monthly bills above Rs. 8,000 for many households due to geysers and heaters, getting an early look at your SSGC bill — rather than waiting for the printed version to arrive in the mail — can be the difference between paying on time and getting hit with a 5% late surcharge. This guide walks you through the entire process of checking, downloading, and paying your SSGC bill online.</p>

    <div class="bg-primary-50 border-l-4 border-primary-600 p-4 rounded-lg mb-8">
      <p class="font-semibold text-primary-800">Quick Answer: Visit <a href="/ssgc-bill/" class="underline">pakistanbill.online/ssgc-bill/</a>, enter your <strong>10-digit SSGC consumer number</strong> (printed on the top-left of any previous bill, labeled "Consumer No."), and your current month's gas bill appears in seconds. Free, no login, no app required.</p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">What is SSGC and Where Does It Operate?</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">SSGC was incorporated in 1955 and is headquartered in Karachi. The company's franchise area covers the entire provinces of <strong>Sindh</strong> and <strong>Balochistan</strong>, plus a few pockets of southern Punjab. The gas is sourced primarily from fields in Sindh (Mari, Qadirpur, Kandhkot) and Balochistan (Sui, Pirkoh, Uch) and transported through a 3,500+ km transmission network. Major cities served include:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 mb-6 list-disc list-inside">
      <li><strong>Sindh:</strong> Karachi (partial), Hyderabad, Mirpurkhas, Nawabshah, Sukkur, Larkana, Khairpur, Jacobabad, Dadu, Thatta</li>
      <li><strong>Balochistan:</strong> Quetta, Khuzdar, Sibi, Zhob, Loralai, Chaman, Turbat, Gwadar, Pasni</li>
      <li><strong>Punjab (pockets):</strong> Rahim Yar Khan, Bahawalpur, Dera Ghazi Khan (southern Punjab belt)</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-6">If your gas connection is in any of these cities or districts, SSGC is your supplier. SNGPL handles the rest of Punjab, KP, and AJK — including Lahore, Islamabad, Peshawar, and Multan. The two companies are entirely separate; you cannot pay an SNGPL bill at an SSGC office and vice versa.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Step-by-Step: How to Check Your SSGC Bill Online</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">The online SSGC bill check process takes under 30 seconds if you have your consumer number handy:</p>
    <ol class="space-y-4 text-neutral-600 mb-6 list-decimal list-inside">
      <li><strong>Find your 10-digit SSGC consumer number.</strong> Open any previous SSGC bill. The consumer number is printed in bold on the <strong>top-left</strong> of the bill, just below your name and address. It is 10 digits long and labeled "Consumer No." or "Account No." — different from your meter number.</li>
      <li><strong>Open the SSGC bill checker.</strong> Go to <a href="/ssgc-bill/" class="text-primary-600 underline">pakistanbill.online/ssgc-bill/</a>. The page is mobile-friendly and works on slow 2G connections too — important for users in remote parts of Balochistan.</li>
      <li><strong>Enter the 10-digit consumer number.</strong> Type the number carefully. SSGC consumer numbers are digits-only — no letters or dashes. If you copy-paste, make sure no extra spaces are included.</li>
      <li><strong>Click "Check Bill".</strong> Your SSGC bill loads in 2–4 seconds. The page displays: consumer name, address, billing month, MMBTU consumed, current charges, arrears, total payable, and due date.</li>
      <li><strong>Download the PDF duplicate.</strong> Click "Download PDF" to save a copy. The PDF includes the barcode and is accepted at all banks and payment retailers.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">What Information Shows on Your SSGC Bill?</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">SSGC bills have several unique fields that differ from electricity bills. Here's what you'll see:</p>
    <div class="bg-neutral-900 text-green-400 font-mono rounded-xl p-5 mb-6 text-sm overflow-x-auto">
      <p class="text-neutral-400 text-xs mb-2">// SSGC Bill — Top Section</p>
      <p>┌─────────────────────────────────────┐</p>
      <p>│  Sui Southern Gas Company Bill          │</p>
      <p>│  ┌────────────────────────────────┐    │</p>
      <p>│  │ Consumer Name: [Your Name]     │    │</p>
      <p class="text-yellow-300">│  │ <strong>Consumer No: 0123456789</strong>      │    │ ← 10-digit</p>
      <p>│  │ Address: [Your Address]        │    │</p>
      <p>│  │ Tariff: Domestic (R)           │    │</p>
      <p>│  │ Meter Reading: 1245 HM³        │    │</p>
      <p>│  │ Previous Reading: 1180 HM³     │    │</p>
      <p>│  │ Consumption: 65 HM³ (2.4 MMBTU)│    │</p>
      <p>│  │ Current Bill: Rs. 4,180        │    │</p>
      <p>│  │ Gas Infra Surcharge: Rs. 250   │    │</p>
      <p>│  │ Total Payable: Rs. 4,430       │    │</p>
      <p>│  │ Due Date: 22-June-2026         │    │</p>
      <p>│  └────────────────────────────────┘    │</p>
      <p>│  [████████ BARCODE ████████]            │</p>
      <p>└─────────────────────────────────────┘</p>
    </div>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-6">Watch out for two SSGC-specific charges: <strong>Gas Infrastructure Surcharge (GIS)</strong> — a small per-MMBTU fee that funds pipeline expansion — and <strong>RLNG surcharge</strong> if your area is partly supplied by imported LNG. Both are regulated by OGRA and apply nationwide.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">How to Pay Your SSGC Bill</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">SSGC bills can be paid through every major payment channel in Pakistan. Pick the one that's most convenient:</p>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
      <table class="w-full text-sm border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg">
        <thead class="bg-neutral-100">
          <tr>
            <th class="text-left p-3 border-b border-neutral-200">Method</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 border-b border-neutral-200">Where</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 border-b border-neutral-200">Fee</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 border-b border-neutral-200">Time</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-neutral-200">
          <tr><td class="p-3">JazzCash</td><td class="p-3">App → Utility Bills → Gas → SSGC</td><td class="p-3">Free</td><td class="p-3">Instant</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3">EasyPaisa</td><td class="p-3">App → Bills → Gas → SSGC</td><td class="p-3">Free</td><td class="p-3">Instant</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3">Bank mobile apps</td><td class="p-3">HBL, UBL, MCB, Alfalah, Meezan</td><td class="p-3">Free</td><td class="p-3">Instant</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3">1Bill / Infinia</td><td class="p-3">Any retailer, ATM</td><td class="p-3">Rs. 30–50</td><td class="p-3">Same day</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3">Bank branch</td><td class="p-3">HBL, UBL, MCB, NBP, Bank Alfalah</td><td class="p-3">Free</td><td class="p-3">Same day</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3">SSGC cash counter</td><td class="p-3">Karachi HQ or regional offices</td><td class="p-3">Free</td><td class="p-3">Same day</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3">NADRA e-Sahulat</td><td class="p-3">Any NADRA center</td><td class="p-3">Rs. 30</td><td class="p-3">Same day</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-6">Late payment of SSGC bills incurs a 5% surcharge in the first month and additional interest thereafter. Worse, accounts in arrears for 60+ days may be disconnected — reconnection costs Rs. 1,500 and takes 5–7 working days.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">SSGC Customer Service & Emergencies</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">SSGC's customer service is critical because gas leaks are life-threatening. Memorize these numbers if you're an SSGC consumer:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 mb-6 list-disc list-inside">
      <li><strong>Central helpline (24/7):</strong> 1199 from any mobile — handles billing queries AND gas leak emergencies</li>
      <li><strong>Karachi complaint cell:</strong> 021-99203022</li>
      <li><strong>Hyderabad region:</strong> 022-9201212</li>
      <li><strong>Quetta region:</strong> 081-9201119</li>
      <li><strong>Sukkur region:</strong> 071-9201234</li>
      <li><strong>Online complaint:</strong> ssgc.com.pk → "Customer Services" → "Complaints" — generates tracking number</li>
      <li><strong>Email:</strong> info@ssgc.com.pk (general) / emergency@ssgc.com.pk (gas leaks)</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-6"><strong>⚠ Gas leak safety:</strong> If you smell gas (rotten-egg odor), do NOT switch on any electrical appliance, light a match, or use your phone inside the house. Open all windows, evacuate everyone, then call 1199 from outside. SSGC's emergency team reaches within 30 minutes in cities and 2 hours in rural areas.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Tips to Reduce Your SSGC Bill</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-3 text-neutral-600 mb-6 list-disc list-inside">
      <li><strong>Use a gas geyser with auto-ignition</strong> instead of pilot-light models — saves 15–20% gas monthly.</li>
      <li><strong>Lower geyser thermostat to 50°C</strong> in summer. Most geysers are set at 65°C+ which wastes gas.</li>
      <li><strong>Turn off gas heaters when sleeping</strong> — a 4-hour running room heater uses as much gas as a week of cooking.</li>
      <li><strong>Switch to a convection heater</strong> if you use gas heating. They cost more upfront but use 30% less gas.</li>
      <li><strong>Get your meter inspected every 3 years</strong> — old gas meters under-read for the first few years then over-read as they age.</li>
      <li><strong>Apply for a solar water heater</strong> — SSGC offers rebates on connection fees for consumers who install solar water heating systems.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-heading font-bold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 mb-10">
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">How to check SSGC gas bill online?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Go to pakistanbill.online/ssgc-bill/ and enter your 10-digit SSGC consumer number. Your Sui Southern Gas bill loads instantly — free, no login required.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Which provinces does SSGC cover?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">SSGC covers Sindh (excluding parts served by K-Electric) and Balochistan. Major cities include Hyderabad, Sukkur, Larkana, Quetta, Khuzdar, and Sibi. SNGPL handles the rest of Pakistan.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">How to pay SSGC gas bill?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Pay SSGC bill through JazzCash (Utility Bills → Gas → SSGC → 10-digit consumer number), EasyPaisa, bank mobile apps, or any 1Bill-affiliated retailer. Also payable at HBL, UBL, MCB, NBP, and Bank Alfalah branches.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">What is the SSGC helpline?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">SSGC helpline is 1199 from any mobile. For gas leak emergencies in Sindh/Balochistan, call 1199 immediately and evacuate the area. Regional complaint cells: 021-99203022 (Karachi), 081-9201119 (Quetta).</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Can I download a duplicate SSGC bill?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Yes. Visit pakistanbill.online/ssgc-bill/, enter your 10-digit consumer number, and click 'Download PDF'. The duplicate is valid for payment at all banks and retailers.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Why is my SSGC bill higher in winter?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Gas consumption rises sharply in winter due to geysers and room heaters. SSGC also applies a winter slabs tariff (effective Nov–Feb) where per-MMBTU price increases for consumption above 0.5 HM³ per month. Reduce bills by using efficient geysers and lowering thermostat settings.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">What is the difference between SSGC and SNGPL?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">SSGC supplies gas to Sindh and Balochistan (southern Pakistan). SNGPL supplies Punjab, KP, and AJK (northern Pakistan). They are separate companies with separate consumer databases — you cannot pay an SNGPL bill at an SSGC office.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">What should I do if I smell gas inside my house?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Do NOT switch on/off any electrical appliance, light a match, or use your phone inside. Open all windows, evacuate everyone in the house, then call SSGC emergency 1199 from OUTSIDE the house. The emergency team usually arrives within 30 minutes in cities.</div></details>
    </div>

